-- Latvian Parliament Backs Higher Retirement Age Starting 2014
-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 2012-06-14T14:36:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/latvian-parliament-backs-higher-retirement-age-starting-2014.html
Latvia’s Parliament passed
legislation to raise the retirement age starting 2014 to shore
up public finances as the Baltic nation’s population ages.  The 100-member legislature backed boosting the pension age
to 65 from 62 for both men and women in three-month increments
until 2024, according to a statement today from Parliament.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  